(Specifically: Current/Most Recent Employer and Position) | q16: Would you be interested in taking part in IAG's Alumni Mentorship Program? 


We are re-opening the IAG Alumni Mentorship Program! During this program, we will connect you with a current IAG Portfolio Team member. We are aiming for mentors and mentees to have one-on-one connections, and we are expecting communication a couple of times per semester to avoid overburdening your schedule. We are opening up this program to alumni in other geographic areas as well who are willing to communicate over phone or email. Our members would really appreciate to learn from your personal/professional journeys! | q20: Would you be interested in participating in IAG's Alumni Workshop Series? 



Our IAG Alumni Workshop Series this spring is aimed at taking advantage of the alumni's vast wealth of knowledge as a catalyst for mentorship. The structure of these workshops are highly flexible, ranging from alumni-led lectures, case walkthroughs, panels, to fireside chats. We see these workshops as educational in nature, taught by members of alumni to the current club members. Not only can these teach-ins be highly educational, they are also a great way for members interested in a specific topic to touch base with you all afterward. We are hoping to host these workshops during Wednesday Common Hour (12:30 PM - 13:30 PM ET), though the exact length of the presentation is up to your discretion.


*All events will be held remotely unless permitted by NYU | q17: Would you be interested in taking part in IAG's Battle of the Alumni pitch?
 

We would like to bring back an IAG tradition since 2011 – Battle of the Alumni – in which two alumni will work with current P-Team members to argue two different investment theses on the same company. This would be a great opportunity for P-Team members to learn from alumni! 
*All events will be held remotely unless permitted by NYU | q19: Would you be interested in an in-person alumni event in NYC (if restrictions allow)?
 

*All events will be held remotely unless permitted by NYU
